          "INC-SPECT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                ".Proton beam energy adjusted so to be 30 and 100 KeV",
                " above the 7-Li(p,n)7-Be reaction threshold 1.881 MeV.",
                " In this way, continuous neutron spectra in the proper",
                " energy range for S-process studies were obtained,",
                " ranging from 3 to 100 and from 3 to 225 keV."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                ".The samples were prepared from isotopically enriched",
                " oxide powder-Lu2-O3 and Hf-O2 canned in the aluminum",
                " boxes.  Samples were heated to 1200 degree K for",
                " 15-min to eliminate any water contaminations. During",
                " the final heating the pellets shrank slightly.",
                " Immediately after cooling, the actual samples were",
                " prepared by canning the pellets into air tight",
                " aluminum  cylinders with 0.2-mm thick walls.",
                ".Apart from the two lutetium or five hafnium samples, a",
                " gold sample in an identical can was used for measuring",
                " the neutron flux, and an empty can served for",
                " determining the sample-independent background."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ADD-RES": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "COMP"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ".The CASINO/GEANT version of the MONTE CARLO code",
                " were used for simulations of experimental setup.",
                " Available from Apostolakis J., CERN, GEANT library,",
                " www.cern.ch  ."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "D4PI"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ". The Karlsruhe 4pi-Barium-Fluoride detector via",
                "        the prompt gamma-rays consisting of 42 hexa-",
                " and penta-gonal crystals forming a spherical shell",
                " of Ba-F2 with 10 cm inner radius and 15 cm thickness",
                " The energy resolution of the individual crystals were",
                " normalized by means of actual spectra and equal to",
                " 7.% at 2.5MeV gamma energy, time resolution 500 ps"
              ]
            }
          ],
